payload.text:
I will restructure the application initialization to robustly handle module loading errors. By decoupling the dependencies and using dynamic imports, the application will be able to start up and, if any specific component fails, report the error directly on the screen instead of failing silently with a white screen.

1.  **Refactor `index.tsx`**: Remove the static import of `App`. Use `import()` (dynamic import) to load the app. This ensures the main script executes immediately and can catch any errors during the loading of `App.tsx`.
2.  **Refactor `data/sayings.ts`**: Remove the external dependency on `types.ts`. This eliminates a common point of failure in relative path resolution.
3.  **Refactor `App.tsx`**: Define the `Saying` interface locally. This makes the component self-contained.

# Updated files:

## index.tsx

Switched to dynamic imports to prevent "white screen of death" if module resolution fails. Now catches and displays errors on screen.

```tsx
import React from 'react';
import { createRoot } from 'react-dom/client';

const container = document.getElementById('root');

if (!container) {
  document.body.innerHTML = '<div style="color:red;padding:20px;">Root element not found</div>';
} else {
  // Show a loading indicator while the app module is being fetched
  const root = createRoot(container);

  // Use dynamic import to isolate the App component loading
  // This prevents the entire script from failing if App.tsx has a resolution error
  import('./App')
    .then(({ default: App }) => {
      root.render(
        <React.StrictMode>
          <App />
        </React.StrictMode>
      );
    })
    .catch(error => {
      console.error("Failed to load App module:", error);
      // Fallback UI to show the error
      container.innerHTML = `
        <div style="
          display: flex; 
          flex-direction: column; 
          align-items: center; 
          justify-content: center; 
          height: 100vh; 
          font-family: sans-serif; 
          color: #8E1600; 
          background-color: #FDFBF7; 
          text-align: center;
          padding: 20px;
        ">
          <h2 style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Unable to load application</h2>
          <p style="color: #2C2C2C; margin-bottom: 20px;">An error occurred while initializing.</p>
          <pre style="
            padding: 15px; 
            background: #eee; 
            border-radius: 8px; 
            font-size: 12px; 
            color: #333; 
            max-width: 100%; 
            overflow-x: auto;
            text-align: left;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
          ">${error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)}</pre>
        </div>
      `;
    });
}
```

