The "SecurityError: The operation is insecure" typically occurs when an application tries to modify the browser's URL history (via `window.history.pushState` or `replaceState`) from inside a sandboxed environment (like an iframe or a locally opened file) that restricts these actions.

To fix this and ensure the app loads even if URL updates are blocked, I will wrap all history API calls in `try-catch` blocks. This ensures the visual content updates even if the "deep link" feature fails.

# Updated files:

## App.tsx

Wrapped `window.history` operations in `try-catch` blocks to prevent the application from crashing in restricted browser environments.

